In case you missed it, here are the top Sport stories of the week: 1. BUCCANEERS TIE DOWN MHANGO! Orlando Pirates have moved quickly to extend their option to extend star striker Gabadinho Mhango contract, according to the player's agent Mike Makaab. 2. BREAKING: NASCIMENTO PART WAYS WITH DOWNS! Mamelodi Sundowns have paved the way for new signing, Bolivian Erwin Saavedra, by sacrificing Brazilian Ricardo Nascimento, as they balance their required foreign quota. 3. WARRIORS CLINCH COMPACT CUP! Warriors were crowned the champions of the inaugural DStv Compact Cup after they beat Coastal United 2-1 in the final at the FNB Stadium on Saturday afternoon. 4. USUTHU BOSS MISSES OUT ON STAR STRIKER! Amazulu president Sandile Zungu says they were interested in signing Maritzburg United outgoing striker Bongokuhle Hlongwane. 5. PSL BLOCKS LEOPARDS' MOVE Black Leopards' wish to occupy the Malamulele Stadium immediately has been dealt a massive blow.